register.description: IP Revision Identifier (X.Y.R) Used by software to track features, bugs, and compatibility

bitfield.description: Configuration of the local initiator state management mode. By definition, initiator may generate read/write transaction as long as it is out of STANDBY state.

bitenum.description: Force-standby mode: local initiator is unconditionally placed in standby state. Backup mode, for debug only.

bitfield.description: Configuration of the local target state management mode. By definition, target can handle read/write transaction as long as it is out of IDLE state.

bitenum.description: Force-idle mode: local target's idle state follows (acknowledges) the system's idle requests unconditionally, that is, regardless of the IP module's internal requirements. Backup mode, for debug only.
No-idle mode: local target never enters idle state. Backup mode, for debug only.

Smart-idle mode: local target's idle state eventually follows (acknowledges) the system's idle requests, depending on the IP module's internal requirements. IP module shall not generate (IRQ- or DMA-request-related) wakeup events.

Smart-idle wakeup-capable mode: local target's idle state eventually follows (acknowledges) the system's idle requests, depending on the IP module's internal requirements. IP module may generate (IRQ- or DMA-request-related) wakeup events when in idle state. Mode is only relevant if the appropriate IP module 'swakeup' output(s) is (are) implemented.

bitfield.description: Sensitivity to emulation (debug) suspend input signal.

bitenum.description: IP module is not sensitive to emulation suspend

register.description: Per-event raw interrupt status vector, line #0. Raw status is set even if event is not enabled. Write 1 to set the (raw) status, mostly for debug.

Per-event 'enabled' interrupt status vector, line #0. Enabled status is not set unless event is enabled. Write 1 to clear the status after interrupt has been serviced (raw status gets cleared, that is, even if not enabled).
Per-event interrupt enable bit vector, line #0. Write 1 to set (enable interrupt). Readout equal to corresponding _CLR register.
Per-event interrupt enable bit vector, line #0. Write 1 to clear (disable interrupt). Readout equal to corresponding _SET register.

register.description: CPU Status Register provides information on the progress of the CPU execution

bitfield.description: Set to 1 when Step() Local Interconnect command is received. Set to 1 when SyncBox new task command is received. Set to 0 when Local Interconnect writes 0 to this bit field.
This bit is set to '1' when in Debug mode, an EndOfPgm instruction or the last instruction of ProgramBuffer has been reached.
This bit is set to '1' when a Stop() command is received. This bit is set to '0' when a Step() command is received.

Set when a Local Interconnect read to the Program Memory, or an Local Interconnect write are perfromed while the IME3 is still in the EXECUTING state. Reset when the IME3 is is the INITIALIZED or COMPLETED state and a step command is received.
Indicates that module has received a Local Interconnect Signal1 Command. Reset by Wait_On_Signal_1() api.
Indicates that module is waiting for Local Interconnect Signal1 Command. Set by Wait_On_Signal_1() api. Reset when ReceivedSignal0 is set (by Signal1 Local Interconnect command).
Indicates that module has received a Local Interconnect Signal0 Command. Reset by Wait_On_Signal_0() api.
Indicates that module is waiting for Local Interconnect Signal0 Command. Set by Wait_On_Signal_0() api. Reset when ReceivedSignal0 is set (by Signal0 Local Interconnect command).
Address of the instruction currently issued.
When set to 1, cycle counting is enabled. When set to 0, cycle counting is disabled.
Writing 0 results in no effect. Writing 1 results in clearing CycleCount to 0. Always read as 0.
Incremets at each cycle if cycleCountEnable equals 1 and if CpuState is EXECUTING. Reset when writing 1 to bit 30 (CycleCountReset) Reset upon receiving a Stop() Local Interconnect command.
